yes I know what they are. Use them all the time. But since the post is about if I imagine it&#x27;s about things like<p><pre><code>  if( x < 0 || x > 5 )
    throw new ArgumentOutOfRange();
  if( y == nullptr )
    thwrow new NullRefException();
</code></pre>
which should imo be something like<p><pre><code>  Contract.AssertInRange( x, 0, 5 );
  Contract.AssertNotNull( y );</code></pre>
